</title>
<subSubSection id="3438A6C4E4B2F9E28F54C33AF980AB1B" pageId="null" pageNumber="551" type="description">
<paragraph id="897C8DB9D9E3564590C92446CFBA9B32" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis id="8ADDE71102218D30166CC9B7BD2A0DA3" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<normalizedToken id="3FA268B6035CC365BE039D31A50BB10C" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
oberseits fast kahl
</emphasis>
, unterseits zerstreut bis (besonders auf dem Mittelnerv) dicht behaart. 
<emphasis id="4A19195A7FD86182F315D56D23DD2955" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<normalizedToken id="43962975A99027C1980F2A0454939D0E" originalValue="Blütenköpfe" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Bluetenkoepfe</normalizedToken>
2-2,5 cm im Durchmesser.
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="1C94AF87D99130E041D7AF4DF95CC278" originalValue="Hüllblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Huellblaetter</normalizedToken>
0,7-1,1 cm lang, bis auf 
<normalizedToken id="155EB4C42ED5FB1E36DD3791891BC029" originalValue="½-¼" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">1/2-1/4</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="46EFC1846D4ABA87B9E5BD07EBDFE5BC" originalValue="handförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">handfoermig</normalizedToken>
geteilt, zerstreut behaart. 
<normalizedToken id="3EF7E327F30CAC01282A866DE207B904" originalValue="Kelchröhre" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Kelchroehre</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm lang, zerstreut behaart; 
<emphasis id="E521F7409EFBDCC3198B6E342AD414A7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<normalizedToken id="BB15E231F13CDE3400E3F284809B1D2A" originalValue="Kelchzähne" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Kelchzaehne</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm lang
</emphasis>
, 
<normalizedToken id="8BD3399983502A59C1C67A9E69E6A1C2" originalValue="±" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">+/-</normalizedToken>
gleich lang. 
<emphasis id="CA58D53832BD914D50398C55B014167B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Krone 1-1,4 cm lang</emphasis>
, hell- bis dunkelrosa. - 
<normalizedToken id="32B1AB22FE87E46FB61E82AA0568B58C" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="BBF05675A4F43839C975B4CA05917DE0" originalValue="Später" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Spaeter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="8CA4A9D7845181F875A6E2E84507B531" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="6EBCB9851EAE0ACCB9702CC294DC4C42" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="330DDAACE5D92DAA6239CBC9F9D70405" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis id="8FD5304EA2011A541CCF493216F67ACA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="48EE8005DACDE36FAAE9EE75F4AE58C1" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">28:</emphasis>
Material aus Jugoslawien (Favarger 1965).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DB97334727CCF232EBE6BCF21F84AB5E" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis id="7B039C13328C165FEEA04FCA11DC1F84" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Standort.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="E612CE2581C4CD747155A928BE0E3268" originalValue="Ähnlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Aehnlich</normalizedToken>
wie 
<taxonomicName id="81D9A012DA5708430BF61279D72EA1A1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Anthyllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="551" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="montana">
<emphasis id="2FF9B1EE201BAA74C05CE55C280B5ADD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">A. montana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 2a).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8ACFA96925A93B8ED33C4949E14CEC20" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis id="8D042D6DC7B4C5809FDAB02E48C8FD8B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
Verbreitung. Mittel- und 
<normalizedToken id="2D128DB8058FA8EA8FBD22859D65AE13" originalValue="südeuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">suedeuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Gebirgspflanze
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="20BA6D0885F2437C7F0939AF5423C4A7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<normalizedToken id="CF8636BB1C25A13D9D29FD820C3187A6" originalValue="östlich" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">oestlich</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
)
<emphasis id="76C5A3046F17158F48EAB861B913B4A7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">:</emphasis>
Ostalpen, Karpaten, Gebirge der Balkanhalbinsel (
<normalizedToken id="A4AF0F20D91B85397E443B528B4C82F7" originalValue="südwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">suedwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Bulgarien und Griechenland). Verbreitungskarte von 
<normalizedToken id="7BA1F920F4375ED52B64F9D8110FD353" originalValue="Merxmüller" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">Merxmueller</normalizedToken>
(1952). - Im Gebiet: Comerseegebiet (Griante, Generoso?, Val Colla?), 
<normalizedToken id="A18081350C56BB6C29BADB98E1DFAFAF" originalValue="irrtümliche" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">irrtuemliche</normalizedToken>
Angaben aus dem Veltlin (Monte Braulio, Campendola), Bergamasker Alpen (Val Seriana).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5AD46C9BDDC0E512A7199FFFE93B0628" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
<emphasis id="1423C8829BA28DD78231367D0D9C1A62" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">
Bemerkungen. 
<taxonomicName id="878DF5A0379755657CEE7C03827880F5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Anthyllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="551" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jacquinii">A. Jacquinii</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
besitzt im Gebiet meist dunklere Kronen als typische Exemplare im 
<normalizedToken id="BFBF97444873D8062E8864D38D1398AF" originalValue="östlicheren" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">oestlicheren</normalizedToken>
Verbreitungsgebiet und wird deshalb oft als 
<taxonomicName id="74BE9B12BBC5660A4E47B7E2E53E5DC0" authority="Vukot." authorityName="Vukot." form="atropurpurea" pageId="null" pageNumber="551" rank="form">
f. 
<emphasis id="A22050C9B2C6AEB04750274C245C232A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="551">atropurpurea</emphasis>
Vukot.
</taxonomicName>
bezeichnet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
